This paper focuses on the psychological aspects of building agile teams, which is closely related to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the study involves interviews with coaches, Scrum Masters, and managers responsible for the agile process, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social informatics (cs.SI). The use of surveys to collect data also suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
